<paragraph id="8FE65A6890C5D16059E0CE884A97CEA4" pageId="22" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="C72016472F6D10867CBAC11FB8FC62AA" authorityName="Maas &amp; Westra" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Tetrameranthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tetrameranthus trichocarpus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="22" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichocarpus">
<emphasis id="054B00D2AEDE465755B2CA6630384F1B" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="47">Tetrameranthus trichocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4108D07A3A73E47C114C5E5FC9F90189" genus="T." lsidName="T. globuliferus" pageId="22" pageNumber="47" rank="species" species="globuliferus">
<emphasis id="EDF2A34D910640A8D6707C4B7028E7D2" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="47">T. globuliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Westra from Ecuador in leaf shape and in the young twigs covered with brown, stellate hairs, but differs by 5-merous (vs. 6-merous) flowers and hairy (vs. glabrous) monocarps, and also by smaller leaves (16-28 vs. 27-37 cm long).
</paragraph>
